Born in the Deep Woods is the fourth album by Portland-based
Austin-born family performer Red Yarn. The album completes his
Deep Woods trilogy, an epic tale of family and self-discovery in
the American wilderness, told through traditional and original
animal folksongs. Blending American music of all eras from
bluegrass to trance blues to heartland rock'n'roll. Born in the
Deep Woods pushes Red Yarn's creative folklore project into bold
new territory
